{"id":19220,"name":"Tabs Buttoned","category":"app","raw_subcategory":"browser","subcategory":"browser","style_tags":[],"description":"This style transforms tabs into buttons.\r\n\r\nThis style was created with idea to make tabs look better under Linux (it turns out I really don't like default GTK icons and default Firefox theme under Linux) but it turned out that under Windows7 tabs also become very pretty.\r\n\r\nSo, I decided to share my little (really little) work with everybody else.\r\nAlso - I post screenshot from Windows7 since it is much prettier than under Linux.","user":{"id":14809,"name":"xren","email":"redacted","paypal_email":"maxim_belkin@yahoo.com","homepage":null,"about":null,"license":null},"admin_delete_reason_id":null,"updated":"2009-07-03T21:44:13.000Z","weekly_install_count":0,"total_install_count":691,"rating":null,"screenshot_url":"https://userstyles.org/style_screenshots/19220_after.gif?r=1580284869","url":"/styles/19220/tabs-buttoned","discussionsCount":1,"commentsCount":1,"css":"@namespace url(http://www.mozilla.org/keymaster/gatekeeper/there.is.only.xul);\r\n\r\n\r\n.tabbrowser-arrowscrollbox > .scrollbutton-up,\r\n.tabbrowser-arrowscrollbox > .scrollbutton-down,\r\n.tabs-alltabs-button,\r\n.tabs-newtab-button,\r\n.tabbrowser-tab {\r\n    -moz-appearance:button!important;\r\n    margin:1px 0!important; padding:0 3px!important;}\r\n\r\n.tabs-bottom{display:none!important;}\r\n\r\n.tabbrowser-tab * {margin:-4px 0!important;}\r\n.tabs-alltabs-button {padding:0!important; border:0px!important;}\r\n\r\n.tabs-alltabs-button .toolbarbutton-menu-dropmarker {margin: 0 -2px -2px 0!important;}\r\n\r\n.tabbrowser-arrowscrollbox > .scrollbutton-up .toolbarbutton-icon {margin:0 3px 0 2px!important;}\r\n.tabbrowser-arrowscrollbox > .scrollbutton-down .toolbarbutton-icon {margin:0 2px 0 3px!important;}\r\n\r\n.tabbrowser-arrowscrollbox > .scrollbutton-up:active .toolbarbutton-icon{margin:-1px 4px 2px 1px!important;}\r\n.tabbrowser-arrowscrollbox > .scrollbutton-down:active .toolbarbutton-icon{margin:-1px 3px 2px 2px!important;}\r\n\r\n.tab-close-button{-moz-appearance:none!important; margin:-4px 0!important;}\r\n"}